page.title: 14BRAMLEY FRITH
page.content: {BRAMLEY FRITH}is a woodland surrounding a{CENTRAL ELECTRICITY {GENERATING BOARD SUB-STATION}To the east is a railway and to the west is Latchmore Farm and Latchmore Green. The woodland is mostly {DECIDIOUS} i.e.oak,hazel,birch and beech. Bramley Frith has a {NATURE TRAIL.}The Nature Trail follows a 1.75 mile circular route through the woodland,which is indicated by a series of numbered white posts and direction arrows. The woodland is 800 metres at its' longest and 700 metres at its' widest,covering 67 acres. Entery is free but for access to classrooms and toilets bookings must be made in advance with Bramley C.E.Primary School,Bramley Lane,Bramley,Basingstoke,Hants.RG26 5AH.
